An attempted murder investigation has been opened after a person was wounded in a shooting in the CBD. The shooting took place on the corner of Long and Pepper streets around 3.40am on Sunday, News24 reported On Monday, Western Cape police spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana confirmed the shooting. "According to information, there was a fight and the victim was transported to hospital for treatment. No one has been arrested so far." Dave Bryant, ward councillor for the City Bowl, posted on Facebook that a suspect was identified after the shooting and Central City Improvement District security staff passed this information on to police officers. "The two agencies then worked together to quickly block off a vehicle with the suspects inside," Bryant said. Contradicting Rwexana, Bryant said four suspects, one of them in possession of a firearm, were arrested. There has been a deadly battle among security firms to control the nightclub industry.